1573
02:00:19,702 --> 02:00:29,828
Upon further review, this kind of took place over the summer, high school administrators determined that one segment of the policy would be very difficult to enforce.

1574
02:00:30,569 --> 02:00:32,910
And this item deals with the student use of

1575
02:00:33,397 --> 02:00:38,219
cell phones or electronic devices in the hallways between the passing of classes.

1576
02:00:38,979 --> 02:00:42,840
The approved policy has very specific sanctions for violations.

1577
02:00:43,421 --> 02:00:51,023
We want to ensure that if we are going to impose sanctions, that we have the ability to do so consistently and equitably.

1578
02:00:51,083 --> 02:01:01,687
And the headmaster felt that we really didn't have that ability to be consistent and equitable in how we would treat violations.

1579
02:01:02,328 --> 02:01:10,951
So therefore, we're recommending that we amend the policy to allow for the use of the devices in the hallways during passing time.

1580
02:01:11,911 --> 02:01:30,438
And since students are not all necessarily in the cafeteria during lunch periods, the new amended policy speaks to the use of electronic devices during lunch periods in, quote, designated student areas, which would include, in addition to the cafeteria, the gym and the library.

1581
02:01:31,607 --> 02:01:41,051
We have also added some language that wasn't in there before that's specific to the needs of students on special education plans at all grade levels.

1582
02:01:41,911 --> 02:01:54,175
So based on the conversations with the administrators, we are recommending that the school committee replace the previous approved electronic device policy with the amended electronic device policy.

1583
02:01:54,576 --> 02:02:00,978
