02:07:10,421 --> 02:07:14,765
I would agree wholeheartedly with Mr. Benedetto for some of the reasons, but I'd like to also provide some context.

1651
02:07:16,019 --> 02:07:25,584
Like everything we do in public education, we have to reassess the practices and the techniques we utilize every single year, because things change dramatically, specifically in technology, of course.

1652
02:07:26,324 --> 02:07:43,012
So one of the things that we've been really wrestling with is how to address the growing omnipotence of cell phone technology, including technology on watches, on tablets, on small handheld computers, laptops, obviously, and they're everywhere.

1653
02:07:43,612 --> 02:07:50,874
And I would also like to echo Mr. Panandello that a lot of students use it as a calendar, as their appointments.

1654
02:07:51,514 --> 02:07:53,174
I know my children do that as well.

1655
02:07:53,695 --> 02:08:02,677
So we were faced with the task of trying to enforce a policy that we did not think, A, that it was something that was enforceable, and B, perhaps it was something that wasn't.

1656
02:08:03,349 --> 02:08:05,710
impacting public education on the education of students.

1657
02:08:06,110 --> 02:08:11,572
I did reach out to every single community in the area and not one community enforces this rule.

1658
02:08:12,132 --> 02:08:20,195
Many of them told me that we turn a blind eye but none of them enforced it and we'd rather have a frank conversation with students and teach them

1659
02:08:20,755 --> 02:08:29,202
the importance of technology and how to utilize it as adults, because we agree that adults are walking around with this technology, including the faculty members and myself.

1660
02:08:29,582 --> 02:08:34,246
I know I use my cell phone on a daily basis, walking through the halls, looking at emails and my schedule.

1661
02:08:34,706 --> 02:08:37,188
So we thought it would be a good opportunity for us to

1662
02:08:38,699 --> 02:08:57,387
address a small area, we're talking about three minutes a day, but in that, allowing students to do that in that period, we also have conversations with them about the importance and really the sacredness of instructional time, and that during classroom time, it's unacceptable to pull out your cell phone, just like it would be to attend a meeting as a professional.

1663
02:08:57,887 --> 02:09:00,208
Unless, of course, the educator allowed that to take place.

1664
02:09:00,749 --> 02:09:03,310
So these are the conversations we have with students on a daily basis.

1665
02:09:03,810 --> 02:09:11,594
Also part of our plan for the future is to address legitimate concerns with technology use and abuse by all of society.

1666
02:09:11,915 --> 02:09:14,696
There is an addictive nature to this and we want to discuss it.

1667
02:09:14,756 --> 02:09:18,158
We have intentions on utilizing advisories for these conversations.

1668
