We also, you mentioned the basketball court being opened.

1669
02:09:22,059 --> 02:09:27,780
Interestingly enough, not one cell phone's out in the basketball court, because we opened up a place for students to be active.

1670
02:09:28,140 --> 02:09:31,321
In the cafeteria, we do allow it, and most students are very quiet on how to utilize it.

1671
02:09:31,801 --> 02:09:35,902
I would recommend that anyone come to the school and look through the halls, especially school community members.

1672
02:09:36,222 --> 02:09:38,363
There's no change in behavior in the hallways.

1673
02:09:38,983 --> 02:09:41,604
It's not as if we're advocating for students to pull out their cell phone.

1674
02:09:41,904 --> 02:09:47,245
We're just addressing and allowing it to happen because we're being practical and we're trying to use it as an educational opportunity.

1675
02:09:49,291 --> 02:09:49,431
Ms.

1676
02:09:49,451 --> 02:09:49,934
Van De Kloot.

1677
02:09:51,120 --> 02:09:52,064
I appreciate your work.

1678
02:09:52,608 --> 02:10:12,071
Dr. Perillo, I have to say the only thing which is just, well, I have two different things that's just gnawing at me, and I'll vote to go along with this, but the other day I overheard a conversation between two parents, and one of them said, my son has already called or texted me six times, and it was only 10.30 in the morning.

1679
02:10:12,651 --> 02:10:20,253
And she said, I wish they wouldn't allow this, because it was clearly, where is that separation between child and parent?

1680
02:10:20,313 --> 02:10:21,993
And I see that as a growing,

1681
02:10:22,508 --> 02:10:38,469
concern, we talk about helicopter parents, we talk about, you know, kids, they're just, the advent of this ease in 24-7 technology has also meant for some kids not being as, gaining their independence.

1682
02:10:39,310 --> 02:10:39,770
And so I

1683
02:10:40,871 --> 02:11:02,945
