1684
02:11:03,566 --> 02:11:10,010
And, you know, when you're in the kind of environment where I work, we need to impress upon

1685
02:11:10,600 --> 02:11:19,813
our students what's appropriate and they're just so used to having ready access that when that cell phone buzzes, they're thinking they can be there.

1686
02:11:20,153 --> 02:11:21,695
If I could respond to that first question.

1687
02:11:22,296 --> 02:11:25,300
I agree with you completely and I think it's a societal concern and issue.

1688
02:11:26,061 --> 02:11:26,622
It is also

1689
02:11:27,543 --> 02:11:36,550
I don't think it is reasonable to expect a school to make that stand in the hallways in an equitable manner, which is consistent, thanks to real concern.

1690
02:11:36,850 --> 02:11:43,675
But we also, I would like to emphasize that students are using their cell phones, even in schools that have a zero cell phone policy.

1691
02:11:43,695 --> 02:11:48,279
There's not a school, not a high school student that's not accessing their phone if they have one.

1692
02:11:48,539 --> 02:11:52,602
They leave the classroom, they go to the bathroom, they sneak it in every opportunity they have.

1693
02:11:52,978 --> 02:12:02,123
what we're having a change in the mindset of students is that we understand that, but there are certain times, sacred times, like classroom instruction, where it's completely unacceptable.

1694
02:12:02,183 --> 02:12:08,006
And like mentioned earlier, that includes going to the bathroom during classroom time.

1695
02:12:08,146 --> 02:12:11,288
So we truly enforce the hallways during classroom time.

1696
02:12:11,708 --> 02:12:19,673
